# Output Format

Produce a **UAT Report** in the exact format below. A code-level validator will reject the report if structural fields are missing.

```markdown
# UAT Report

## Overall Result: PASS | FAIL

## Aggregate
- Total ACs: N
- Runtime-verified: X
- Spec-traced: Y
- Skipped: Z

## Summary
<brief overall assessment>

## Feature: [F001] <name>
### [AC-001] <acceptance criterion text>
- **Result:** PASS | FAIL
- **Verification mode:** runtime | spec_trace | skipped
- **Driver:** {{ driver_enum }}
- **Evidence:**
  - <concrete observation per assertion — no vague language>
- **Artifacts:** (relative paths under .agentic-dev/uat/{{ run_id }}/evidence/{{ track_name }}/)
  - <path>
- **Notes:** <optional>

## Cross-Feature Tests
### <test description>
- **Result:** PASS | FAIL
- **Verification mode:** runtime | spec_trace | skipped
- **Driver:** {{ driver_enum }}
- **Evidence:**
  - <observation>

## Recommendations
- <any improvements or concerns not covered by acceptance criteria>
```

**Invariants enforced by the validator (structural, not optional):**

- A PASS verdict requires at least one AC with `Verification mode: runtime` (when `uat_mode: full`).
- Any AC with `Result: PASS` and `Verification mode: runtime` MUST have non-empty `Artifacts:` entries.
- If every AC reports `Driver: none`, the overall result cannot be PASS in `uat_mode: full`.
- Every `Result: PASS` entry MUST have non-empty `Evidence:` bullets. Vague or generic evidence will be flagged.

Set `Overall Result: PASS` only if every acceptance criterion passes AND the runtime-evidence rules above hold. Otherwise FAIL.
